               <note type="description">A letter written to IA’s philosopher contemporary, Fakhr al-Dīn al-Rāzī, calling him to return from the pursuit of intellectual knowledge to spiritual intuition.</note>
               <note type="biblioComments">A much copied work, of which there are three early mss. though none are definitive. The best is probably Shehit Ali 1341 (c.725H, a good collection with several works taken from originals in the hand of IA). However, the note at the end of this work says “taken from an original” without specifying its nature, so it is not certain that it was in IA’s hand. The case for regarded this as a verified work rests on the internal evidence of the text. JC has identified other copies: Kastamonu 2183 fols 31a-31b (704H); Köprülü, Fazıl Ahmed Pş., ??, 87-92 s (739H?)</note>
